.TH "LIGHTNING-PEER-CONNECT" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-peer-connect \- connect to a Lightning network peer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning peer-connect
.I pubkey@host[:port]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Connects to a Lightning peer at the given address.
The address must be in the form
.IR pubkey@host:port
or
.IR pubkey@host
(port defaults to 9735).
Returns JSON
.B {"peer_id":"...","connected":true}
on success.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Connection established.
.TP
.B 5
Connection failed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-peer (1),
.BR lightning-peer-disconnect (1),
.BR lightning-peer-list (1)
